Paper: hep-th/9503003

Date: 1995-03-01

Title: Central potential and examples of hidden algebra structure

Authors: Y.Brihaye, N.Devaux and P.Kosinski

Comments: 8 pages, latex, no figures

Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A10 (1995) 4633-4640

We propose two generalisations of the Coulomb potential equation of quantummechanics and investigate the occurence of algebraic eigenfunctions for thecorresponding Scrh\"odinger equations. Some relativistic counterparts of theseproblems are also discussed.